item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickies to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

End of tenancy cleaning service For those moving out of a property we provide professional, comprehensive service, so you get your deposit back , avoid unseemly landlord-tenant disputes and enjoy hassle free moving out.... Read more...
Pre-tenancy service Moving in a property is both exciting and time consuming. Once you moved in you may find the property needs an extra clean, some odd jobs and decorating to be completed.... Read more...
Builders clean You can place your trust with FloraClean to manage your builders clean. We have an extensive experience and expertise in builders and sparkle cleans. Read more...
Carpet cleaning FloraClean is committed to provide high quality carpet cleaning in London and the Home Counties. Read more...
Upholstery cleaning Without realizing you’re sitting on dirt, mist, bacteria. The furniture tends to be the home of many stains and it requires regular maintaining and professional cleaning, so you can protect your investment. Read more...
House clearance Are you moving house or would like to get rid of a single item?! We clear all types and sizes of properties, even where parking is difficult and access is restricted. Read more...
One off spring clean Our one off cleaning service is suitable for those looking for a thorough house spring clean or those who would like to get a domestic cleaner without signing up a contract. Read more...
Handyman Skilled craftsmen painters and handymen who have many years of experience and CSCS. They are trained on how to deliver the fastest and most reliable service and they do so with professionalism.....Read more...
Painting / Decorating We have painted thousands of properties throughout London and surrounding areas. From one room to whole property we offer all aspects of internal and external decorating for both domestic and commercial.Read more....

item.title: End of tenancy cleaning service
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
End of tenancy cleaning service

How to get your deposit back, avoid landlord-tenants disputes and have a stress free moving out?

If you are a moving out of a rented property then you must comply with your tenancy agreement terms in order to get your deposit back in full. You may prefer to do the final clean yourself, but if you are looking for a hassle free moving out at affordable cost  Floraclean is the right end of tenancy cleaning service provider for you. Our team of professional cleaners will carry out an extensive end of tenancy cleaning service at your property and will bring it up to its best shape. We will support you in getting your deposit back in full.

What you will get in return for your business is:

  • - Fully guaranteed service, so if your landlord or estate agent are not entirely happy with any of the areas cleaned you are protected
  • - A dedicated, mobile and experienced team of cleaners. We will come fully equipped, you don’t have to provide anything (but access, water and electricity)
  • - Our supervisor will inspect the property upon completion to make sure the end of tenancy checklist is followed and the place is in its highest standards of cleanliness
  • - Fixed prices, no surprises. Our affordable prices are just from £90.00

 

FloraClean has provided hundreds of tenants and landlords in London with professional end of tenancy cleaning service. We are working closely with major estate agents to make sure every job we attend is carried out in professional manner leaving tenants and landlords satisfied.
Give us a call for a FREE quote and book your slot for hassle free moving out.

End of tenancy check list:


Kitchen

  • Wash and polish all work surfaces.
  • Clean all cupboards (shelves and doors) inside and outside. Remove all old food stuffs, carrier bags etc and dispose of.
  • Clean tops of wall units and underneath them
  • Clean and de-scale sink, taps, wastes and draining areas and polish where required
  • Degrease wall tiles, clean and polish
  • Clean exterior of all appliances including kettle, toaster
  • Internal oven cleaning to remove any of built up grease as well as clean exterior and polish any external chrome
  • Clean oven racks and trays
  • Clean hobs, gas rings and gas control knobs
  • Clean and remove grime from extractor
  • Clean and defrost fridge / freezer and remove any grime, mildew and food
  • Clean washing machine inside and out. Clean rubber at the door and soap drawers
  • Clean dishwasher inside and out (if any)
  • Bins cleaned inside and out
  • Hoover, damp mop clean and polish hard floor and clean skirting boards
  • Internal window cleaning, wipe down window frames, clean doors, tops of doors and door handles
  • Clean and wipe all light switches, light fittings, socket outlets 

 

Bathroom

  • Shower screen de-scaled, cleaned and polished
  • Degrease wall tiles, clean end polish
  • Bath, basin, taps, shower and fittings to be cleaned, de-scaled, dried and polished
  • Toilet to be de-scaled, and brushed clean. Seat and cover to be cleaned and disinfected
  • All soap and shampoo to be removed
  • Clean and polish all mirrors
  • Floors to be washed and polished. If carpet is existent, floors will be vacuumed
  • Clean internally bathroom window (if any)

 

Bedrooms and General areas

  • Dusting throughout including: light fittings and shades, light switches, skirting boards, curtain rails, wall pictures, mirrors, hand rails, stairs, radiators (and behind them if possible)
  • All light furniture moved and vacuumed underneath. Dust skirting boards behind furniture
  • Mattresses to be lifted and vacuumed under
  • Remove cobwebs
  • All other floors to be washed and polished using appropriate type of cleaning liquid
  • All glass (furniture tops, mirrors, picture frames etc) to be cleaned
  • Windows to be cleaned internally and windows sills wiped down
  • All doors and the top of doors to be cleaned. Door handles to be polished
  • Drawers and shelves to be cleared of any rubbish (newspapers and magazines etc.)
